2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 114
BY REPRESENTATIVE MACK
A RESOLUTION
To commend Hannuh Ray of Livingston, Louisiana, on being named 2026 National Little
Miss International Girl Queen.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Hannuh Ray for her achievements and to
commend her on being named the 2026 National Little Miss International Girl Queen; and
WHEREAS, the International Girl Pageant is a premier youth development program
designed to empower, inspire, and celebrate young leaders; the core values of the program
include kindness, friendship, compassion, and respect; and
WHEREAS, the International Girl Pageant is a three-tier system that begins at the
local level and advances through regional and state events, and the program concludes with
the prestigious International Grand Finals; and
WHEREAS, the International Girl Pageant is recognized as one of the most sought-
after programs in youth development, and the program provides a platform for its
participants to shine on stage, in their communities, and at school; and
WHEREAS, Hannuh Ray is a resident of Livingston, Louisiana, who has been named
the 2026 National Little Miss International Girl Queen; she is truly deserving of the highest
recognition for her incredible achievement.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Hannuh Ray of Livingston, Louisiana, on
being named 2026 National Little Miss International Girl Queen and does hereby extend
sincere wishes that she continues her excellent work and prospers in all of her endeavors.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
